The paper addresses a computer vision problem of rain removal from images, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel deep learning architecture for rain removal, which involves multi-task learning and iterative information feedback, indicating the relevance of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of dilated convolution for spatial contextual information, which is a common technique in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
